1
00:00:09,020 --> 00:00:10,950
[Kim Seonghyuk as Kwon Hyukjae]

2
00:00:11,510 --> 00:00:13,200
[Jung Myeongcheol as Yoo Sehyun]

3
00:00:14,440 --> 00:00:16,460
[Kim Hyeonseo as Sung Ho]

4
00:00:19,080 --> 00:00:21,000
[Jung Hyunwoong as Kim Minho]

5
00:00:31,420 --> 00:00:33,330
[Sin and Love]

6
00:00:33,330 --> 00:00:35,340
[Episode 6]

7
00:04:03,020 --> 00:04:04,780
Loyalty never dies.

8
00:04:14,160 --> 00:04:15,480
It never collapses.

9
00:04:24,860 --> 00:04:26,390
I will follow you to the end.

10
00:04:37,820 --> 00:04:39,580
My body still belongs to you.

11
00:04:41,420 --> 00:04:43,680
I will complete the mission resolutely.

12
00:06:28,650 --> 00:06:29,850
People on this street

13
00:06:30,380 --> 00:06:32,110
always call me a smiling tiger.

14
00:06:33,850 --> 00:06:34,860
A smiling tiger?

15
00:06:35,870 --> 00:06:38,060
High-end restaurants
are at the other end of the street,

16
00:06:38,060 --> 00:06:39,790
and my nightclub is at this end.

17
00:06:40,159 --> 00:06:41,360
A clear distinction—

18
00:06:41,580 --> 00:06:43,640
between those upper and lower class.

19
00:06:43,900 --> 00:06:45,920
But the places where those guys above

20
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:47,850
are even more filthy.

21
00:06:49,370 --> 00:06:51,100
I believe in the power of fists.

22
00:06:51,659 --> 00:06:52,990
That's all I believe in.

23
00:06:53,980 --> 00:06:55,280
Being a good person

24
00:06:55,970 --> 00:06:57,770
doesn't mean being protected.

25
00:06:58,880 --> 00:07:00,880
Because I've never been protected.

26
00:07:01,730 --> 00:07:03,050
The truly evil ones

27
00:07:03,240 --> 00:07:04,970
are the ones who dress sharply.

28
00:07:06,470 --> 00:07:07,750
That's why I'm here.

29
00:07:08,790 --> 00:07:09,920
If I don't stop them,

30
00:07:10,370 --> 00:07:11,780
no one will care.

31
00:07:21,230 --> 00:07:21,850
Sit.

32
00:07:23,760 --> 00:07:24,960
No one's here anyway.

33
00:07:50,060 --> 00:07:51,590
I came to ask about the files

34
00:07:51,630 --> 00:07:53,650
Officer Kwon mentioned—

35
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:55,780
when can I get them?

36
00:08:02,660 --> 00:08:03,590
What's the rush?

37
00:08:05,530 --> 00:08:07,280
Aren't cops good at waiting?

38
00:08:09,510 --> 00:08:11,510
I'm not here to wait.

39
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:14,850
Officer Kwon doesn't like to wait.

40
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:19,150
Is that so?

41
00:08:19,880 --> 00:08:21,880
Ah, right.

42
00:08:25,120 --> 00:08:25,920
Kwon Hyukjae.

43
00:08:32,679 --> 00:08:35,350
Kwon Hyukjae...

44
00:09:00,300 --> 00:09:01,360
Russian roulette—

45
00:09:02,490 --> 00:09:03,550
you know it, right?

46
00:09:04,820 --> 00:09:05,850
Once it starts,

47
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:08,660
you don't know how it will end.

48
00:09:12,570 --> 00:09:14,430
Testing me with that kind of thing

49
00:09:15,410 --> 00:09:16,210
is childish.

50
00:09:21,390 --> 00:09:23,190
The moment you pull the trigger,

51
00:09:23,850 --> 00:09:25,810
the world falls completely silent—

52
00:09:25,810 --> 00:09:26,870
not a single sound.

53
00:09:27,810 --> 00:09:28,810
Then you'll realize,

54
00:09:28,810 --> 00:09:31,080
"Oh, I'm actually still alive."

55
00:09:32,350 --> 00:09:34,150
Because you clearly understand

56
00:09:34,870 --> 00:09:36,870
that is the moment closest to death.

57
00:09:37,220 --> 00:09:37,880
Police?

58
00:09:39,820 --> 00:09:40,410
Justice?

59
00:09:43,310 --> 00:09:44,350
What are those?

60
00:09:58,410 --> 00:09:58,910
See?

61
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:01,860
Thrilling, right?

62
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:07,880
Courage

63
00:10:09,950 --> 00:10:11,820
is a word people use all the time.

64
00:10:31,870 --> 00:10:33,280
But the funny thing is,

65
00:10:35,480 --> 00:10:37,620
I never learned that word.

66
00:10:47,650 --> 00:10:49,110
The so-called justice...

67
00:10:50,810 --> 00:10:52,180
is not wavering

68
00:10:53,460 --> 00:10:54,860
even in the face of power.

69
00:11:00,290 --> 00:11:01,090
Everyone says

70
00:11:01,110 --> 00:11:02,050
to respect life

71
00:11:02,090 --> 00:11:03,290
and follow the rules.

72
00:11:04,050 --> 00:11:04,910
But those words

73
00:11:05,500 --> 00:11:07,280
don't work on people like me.

74
00:11:08,580 --> 00:11:10,150
Because from the very beginning,

75
00:11:10,150 --> 00:11:11,780
I had no choice.

76
00:11:13,110 --> 00:11:13,910
Because we...

77
00:11:15,470 --> 00:11:17,200
don't have the right to choose.

78
00:11:25,220 --> 00:11:26,440
Your turn.

79
00:11:28,410 --> 00:11:29,740
What did you want to ask?

80
00:11:30,360 --> 00:11:31,160
About Sung Ho?

81
00:11:34,570 --> 00:11:35,790
I will give you 3 days

82
00:11:36,770 --> 00:11:38,050
to get what you want.

83
00:11:39,250 --> 00:11:40,510
Don't let Sung Ho shake you

84
00:11:40,510 --> 00:11:42,010
and your life up!

85
00:11:43,900 --> 00:11:46,030
It all depends on Officer Kwon's word.

86
00:11:57,230 --> 00:11:57,880
Hey!

87
00:11:59,980 --> 00:12:01,070
Next time,

88
00:12:02,470 --> 00:12:04,400
tell Kwon Hyukjae to come himself.

89
00:12:05,950 --> 00:12:06,440
Got it?

90
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:08,160
As a side note,

91
00:12:09,380 --> 00:12:10,710
I will keep an eye on you.

92
00:12:10,780 --> 00:12:13,780
If you try anything,
I will report to him immediately.

93
00:12:16,250 --> 00:12:16,910
My gun

94
00:12:18,050 --> 00:12:19,450
will not disappoint him.

95
00:12:26,750 --> 00:12:27,430
Is that so?

96
00:12:53,890 --> 00:12:55,060
Three days?

97
00:12:57,830 --> 00:12:59,910
Everyone wants to kill me.

98
00:13:01,910 --> 00:13:02,950
But ironically,

99
00:13:08,860 --> 00:13:10,720
I am also curious about my ending.

100
00:13:51,220 --> 00:13:54,150
Sung Ho, you are not resting
during your break again.

101
00:13:57,170 --> 00:13:59,770
You have been looking
at that file a lot lately.

102
00:14:00,990 --> 00:14:01,990
Are you...

103
00:14:03,280 --> 00:14:05,610
worried about Yoo Sehyun?

104
00:14:06,510 --> 00:14:07,350
Worried?

105
00:14:09,610 --> 00:14:11,070
Who is worried about whom?

106
00:14:13,510 --> 00:14:14,310
Kwon Hyukjae?

107
00:14:21,110 --> 00:14:22,230
I thought...

108
00:14:23,150 --> 00:14:23,780
Well.

109
00:14:24,470 --> 00:14:25,400
I will get going.

110
00:14:39,480 --> 00:14:43,580
[2020.3.17: Accepted a bribe of 50 million KRW from Boss V of Yongsan;
2020.7.22: Accepted 120 million KRW and 5 female hostesses from Office Chief Choi of Gangnam;
2021.2.11: Accepted 3,000 USD from Boss J of Incheon.]

111
00:14:47,440 --> 00:14:48,240
Officer Kwon.

112
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:50,580
The file Sung Ho is reading

113
00:14:50,850 --> 00:14:52,810
is related to you.

114
00:14:55,050 --> 00:14:55,880
However,

115
00:14:56,580 --> 00:14:58,910
this investigation does not look simple.

116
00:15:02,660 --> 00:15:03,100
Yeah.

117
00:15:29,580 --> 00:15:32,290
[Internal Investigation
(Kwon Hyukjae)]

118
00:15:53,930 --> 00:15:55,860
Kwon Hyukjae, it was you all along.

119
00:15:57,330 --> 00:15:58,590
So it wasn't a mistake,

120
00:15:59,880 --> 00:16:01,010
but going easy on me.

121
00:16:57,580 --> 00:16:58,510
Drinking alone?

122
00:17:03,230 --> 00:17:04,079
You are here.

123
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:15,490
Let's drink together.

124
00:17:15,930 --> 00:17:17,460
Why are you drinking alone?

125
00:17:19,010 --> 00:17:19,480
Hmm?

126
00:17:25,619 --> 00:17:27,280
We have some scores to settle.

127
00:17:29,630 --> 00:17:30,350
Right?

128
00:17:44,740 --> 00:17:45,740
Make your choice.

129
00:17:47,740 --> 00:17:49,740
After working together for so long,

130
00:17:50,040 --> 00:17:52,100
it is only right to show some respect.

131
00:18:20,700 --> 00:18:22,280
Fooling around again.

132
00:18:36,190 --> 00:18:36,650
What?

133
00:18:37,550 --> 00:18:38,810
Trying to mess with me?

134
00:18:40,150 --> 00:18:41,050
I told you—

135
00:18:41,910 --> 00:18:42,910
you can't beat me.

136
00:18:44,330 --> 00:18:46,590
You should learn
how to be run away first.

137
00:19:05,950 --> 00:19:06,480
Shoot.

138
00:19:08,640 --> 00:19:10,540
Shoot, you bastard!

139
00:19:23,250 --> 00:19:23,620
Hey.

140
00:19:30,190 --> 00:19:31,250
What are you doing?

141
00:19:46,220 --> 00:19:47,680
I asked what you are doing.

142
00:19:54,570 --> 00:19:56,170
I am sorry.

143
00:20:01,410 --> 00:20:03,110
Damn it.

144
00:20:05,790 --> 00:20:06,380
Let go!

145
00:20:06,770 --> 00:20:07,750
Damn it.

146
00:20:10,440 --> 00:20:10,990
Officer.

147
00:20:12,040 --> 00:20:13,840
I didn't get the file you wanted.

148
00:20:14,470 --> 00:20:15,730
Give me some more time.

149
00:20:15,850 --> 00:20:16,750
No matter what,

150
00:20:16,750 --> 00:20:17,480
I will get it.

151
00:20:18,050 --> 00:20:19,550
Please. Please.

152
00:20:20,050 --> 00:20:22,710
We worked together
for 5 years after all, right?

153
00:20:32,250 --> 00:20:32,650
Hey.

154
00:20:35,770 --> 00:20:36,950
If you didn't get it,

155
00:20:38,210 --> 00:20:40,010
you should have said so earlier.

156
00:20:41,280 --> 00:20:42,280
Why make yourself

157
00:20:44,220 --> 00:20:46,360
so embarrassed?

158
00:20:47,410 --> 00:20:48,020
Right?

159
00:21:09,990 --> 00:21:10,550
Officer.

160
00:21:11,190 --> 00:21:12,850
Give me another chance, okay?

161
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:33,020
[Sin and Love]
